oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Carrie Stull
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Miss Carrie Stull, dressed in white off-the-shoulder dress with a heart-shaped locket around her neck and a white bow in her hair.
Carrie Stull (1883-1906) was from Madison, Tennessee. She married Will T. Jones, a deputy sheriff in Nashville (date unknown). She died April 1, 1906, of septic peritonitis.
